cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the architecture and transmission of marine wireless networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper mentions the challenges of delivering data in hostile marine environments. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is mentioned in the paper as a possible application of the collected big data. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also mentioned as a focus of the possible applications, specifically in sea-surface object detection and marine object recognition. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the challenges of applying the collected data and the need for further exploration.
